const MSG = "Please create a NEW file in this project named slice-01-run-launcher.dc.html for the Run Launcher route. Do NOT modify Crucible Design System.dc.html and do NOT create a new _palette_notes.md (the Graphite Meridian palette already established stands).\n\nUse the palette, type ramp, components, and chrome already defined in Crucible Design System.dc.html. Reference its hex codes exactly. Mount the existing standardized components (InspectButton, ReplayButton, AuditTraceCard, HealthBadge, CostChip, NotYetMeasuredTile) and chrome (halt banner, cost meter, live connection indicator, mock-LLM banner) rather than re-inventing them.\n\nThree customer audiences must be served by every visual decision (per Crucible Design System.dc.html's audience rationale): a bank model risk officer subject to SR 11-7; a code-generation agent vendor engineering lead; a public-sector AI procurement officer.\n\n### Hard product rules\n\n1. Transparency first. Every component must let the user drill into its inner workings: every LLM call shows prompt, raw response, parsed output, tokens, dollars; every oracle vote shows the spec obligation it checked and its reasoning verbatim; every sandbox execution shows stdout and stderr; every persisted action carries a Replay button. Hide only real security risks (API keys, database credentials, sandbox tokens).\n2. No fake values. When a metric has not been measured, render \"Not yet measured\" with a link to the Run Launcher. Never a 0.0 placeholder.\n3. Halt-certification banner is a global red bar at the top whenever white-box recall is below threshold.\n4. The LLM judge oracle is rendered with smaller weight than the four independent oracles and carries a tooltip explaining why.\n\n### Route specification\n\n`/` (Run Launcher). Operator picks a target adapter (Fraud, Code Agent, Research Agent disabled), pastes a sealed YAML specification, sets an attack budget (rounds and dollars), clicks Start. After Start, navigation goes to `/runs/:runId`.\n\n### Deliverable\n\nA single HTML file named slice-01-run-launcher.dc.html containing the page layout plus three stacked mocks in this order:\n1. Happy state (operator has just pasted a valid YAML spec, budget filled in, target picked, Start button enabled).\n2. Empty state (no spec pasted yet, target unpicked, Start button disabled, with prompt text describing what the operator needs to do).\n3. Error state (YAML spec failed to parse, with a specific error message, line number, and a Fix and Re-Validate affordance; the rest of the form preserved).\n\nVisual style: dark theme per the design system. WCAG AA minimum, AAA for body copy where possible. No decorative animation. Sans-serif body, monospace for the YAML paste area and for cost figures. Use Simple Icons logos (cdn.simpleicons.org/<slug>/<hex>) where technology names appear.\n";
